chatgpt_double_star.new_statement: Abortion laws should focus on preventing avoidable harm while acknowledging that people hold sincere, conflicting views about when developing life deserves legal protection. A durable framework keeps early care legal, timely, and confidential; makes emergency and medically necessary treatment unmistakably protected; and sets any later-pregnancy limits in plain, clinically defined terms that do not invite prosecution of patients or good-faith clinicians. Pair legal rules with proven supports—contraception, comprehensive health care, and practical help for parents and adoption—so fewer pregnancies become crises and more families have real options.

Pair legal rules with proven prevention and support—contraception and education, prenatal and postpartum care, and practical help for parents and adoption—so fewer people face crisis pregnancies and fewer abortions occur.
